{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"Plan-review advisory triage (PASS + signed, 0 blocking):\n- G6 (major) — \"add a per-op floor for the agentic verifier instead of raising the GLOBAL default\": user-DIRECTED to double the default step budget; the global default is the documented knob (REBAR_LLM_MAX_STEPS). A per-op floor in the workflow AgentStepRunner is a larger workflow-engine change and out of scope for this directive. Noted as a future option, not adopted.\n- G1G2 (minor) — `docs/config.md:197` (`max_steps = 25` + the tool-call approximation): VALID, will refresh to the new default in this change (added to scope).\n- G1G2 + T8 (minor) — the `tests/interfaces/contracts/test_review_budget.py` module docstring asserting the default is 25: VALID, will refresh the docstring alongside the assertions.\n- E6 (minor) — no AC ties directly to \"no more INDETERMINATE from the 25-step default\": the failure is LLM-path-dependent (not deterministically testable); covered by the default-value AC + the recorded runtime evidence (c38b: 25→INDETERMINATE, 50→PASS). Acknowledged.\n- P6 (minor) — DET ac-quality heuristic; ACs are individually verifiable. Acknowledged.\nScope add from triage: docs/config.md + the test_review_budget.py docstring."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782677518822481001,"uuid":"712e7ad5-993f-4974-8300-c51afe794ce1"}